// ****************************************** 6. Example Upload Flow **********************************************

// User uploads image

// Backend receives file

// File is uploaded to Cloudinary

// Cloudinary returns image URL and public_id

// URL is stored in MongoDB

// User → Backend → Cloudinary → Image URL → MongoDB
// ************************************************* 7. Folder Structure *******************************************

// Example Cloudinary folder structure used in this project:

// doctor-appointment/
//     doctors/
//     users/
//     reports/
// ******************************************** 8. Benefits of Using Cloudinary *******************************

// Secure image storage

// Automatic image optimization

// CDN delivery

// Easy image deletion and management

// Supports images, videos, PDFs, and more

// ********************************************* 9. Example Response From Cloudinary *********************************
// {
//   "public_id": "doctor-appointment/doctors/abc123",
//   "url": "https://res.cloudinary.com/demo/image/upload/v123456/doctor.jpg"
// }
